queue

Class SynchQueue<T extends java.io.Serializable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • queue.SynchQueue<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of elements held in this queue that implements the Serializable interface.

    public class SynchQueue<T extends java.io.Serializable>
extends java.lang.Object
    This SynchQueue is a Specific queue that can use to hold the callers of the poll method until queue gets the items. If one put the item to queue then it will notify to all the caller to get the item from queue as they requested order. We can specify the maximum queue length.
    See Also:
    ExecutionEngine
